    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling output today, anchored by **Yordan Alvarez** (80.29) and **Christian Yelich** (75.84). **Yordan Alvarez** benefits from a strong SP_xERA matchup against Emerson Hancock and a favorable position in the #2 hole, while **Christian Yelich** capitalizes on a generous 4.92 xERA projection for Jake Irvin. **Junior Caminero** remains a vital piece of the heart of the order, sporting the highest SP skill boost (+19%) as he faces Luis Gil. While **Colt Keith** sits at a 68.51, his placement in the #1 spot combined with the favorable +15% SP skill adjustment makes him a primary engine for Runs. We are closely monitoring **Hyeseong Kim** (61.59); while his #8 spot hurts his run-scoring potential, the \"Slow SP Delivery\" bonus specific to his matchup against Kumar Rocker makes him our highest-probability play for a stolen base, a critical metric given our league\u2019s scarcity.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the bench was excluding **Josh Smith** (52.06). While he boasts a significant +14% dynamic platoon edge, the optimizer ultimately favored the higher raw projections and superior lineup order slots of our starting infield. Similarly, **Chase Meidroth** (51.80) was a strong consideration, but the challenging matchup against Kris Bubic suppressed his ceiling just enough to keep him on the bench. We continue to hold **Victor Scott II** (34.48) in reserve; despite his elite speed, the combination of a daunting 2.34 xERA for the opposing starter and a #9 batting order creates a sub-floor projection that does not warrant risking a game cap today. Managers should note that all projected scores remain contingent on official lineups; should any of our hitters like **Dillon Dingler** (48.96) drop further down the order, we may re-evaluate benching them to preserve our limited caps.",
